Comment Event

Users may post threaded comments on a card using kind `30303` regular events.

```javascript
{
    "created_at": 34324234234, //<Unix timestamp in seconds>
    "kind": 30303,
    "content": "This is a comment on the card.",
    "tags": [
        // Binds the comment to the card (used as fetch filter)
        ["a", "30302:<board-creator-pubkey>:<card-d-identifier>"],

        // For a top-level comment, reference the card event id with marker "card"
        ["e", "<card-event-id>", "card"],

        // For a reply to another comment, reference the parent comment event id with marker "reply"
        // and optionally mention the replied-to user with a "p" tag
        // ["e", "<parent-comment-event-id>", "reply"],
        // ["p", "<parent-comment-author-pubkey>"],
    ]
}
```

Comments are regular (non-replaceable) events and must be published with `event.publish()`.  Replies nest one level deep: a reply targets a top-level comment; replies-to-replies are not supported.

### Event Kinds

- 30301: Kanban Board Definition
- 30302: Kanban Card
- 30303: Card Comment

